Fellow West Texans: 

Tomorrow night, I'll be holding a telephone town hall at 7:00 P.M. CT to provide an update on what I have been working on in Washington & hear your feedback on issues important to West Texas.

...That's why I am proud to support a proposed @USDA rule that closes a loophole extending food stamp benefits to those who fail to meet the program’s basic eligibility requirements.

Read more ->  https://bit.ly/2muI0ma  @USDANutrition

With our economy growing at historic rates, unemployment at record lows, & wages & family income rising at the fastest rate in over a decade, it would be a missed opportunity not to reform food stamp policies that too often trap people in a cycle of government dependency...

Our farmers know what's at stake with #USMCA.

They do more than just feed & clothe the American people - they have the bedrock values that this nation was built on.

Let's pass #USMCANow for a better & brighter future for American ag producers. @FarmersForTrade #Rally4USMCA pic.twitter.com/XwyFhUOkVx

My reflections on the 18th anniversary of 9/11

#NeverForget pic.twitter.com/UGAkG2gIGK

While growing our economy & creating new jobs, #USMCA will also send a shot across the bow to Beijing & send a clear message: @realdonaldtrump & Congress are serious about preventing other countries from taking advantage of our workers, businesses, farmers, & manufacturers.

With 170,000+ new jobs, almost $70 billion in economic activity, & an additional $2.2 billion in annual #ag exports on the line, the #CostOfDelay to our farmers, workers, & manufacturers is growing each day. @SpeakerPelosi needs to put #AmericaFirst & bring #USMCA up for a vote.

Had a great meeting today with @USTradeRep, Robert Lighthizer, on #USMCA. 

#Texas leads the nation in trade, & thanks to the leadership of Amb. Lighthizer & @POTUS, this new, fairer deal will ensure that our free trade relationship with Mexico & Canada continues to flourish. pic.twitter.com/KvntaK1iIb

18 years ago today, I was in the White House working for then-President George W. Bush.

As I went about my day, a colleague came in and said, "A plane hit one of the World Trade towers." 

We turned on the TV. 

When the second plane hit, another colleague came into the room... pic.twitter.com/pVV4tPtjG2

We will #NeverForget the evil that came to our shores on this day 18 years ago, how the deadliest attack in our history forever changed our nation, and how it only strengthened our resolve to stand against terror and in defense of freedom and our American values. #NeverForget911 pic.twitter.com/SkI29hwwuR

#USMCA is critical for #Texas, as North American trade supports 1 million jobs in the Lone Star State.
It's a win-win & a no-brainer.

#USMCA will grow our ag exports by an additional $2.2B annually, maintain duty-free access for American farmers in Mexico, & open the Canadian market to American dairy, wheat & poultry products.
